sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>8080/TCP metrics
    participant DNS as Kubernetes DNS<br/>53/UDP
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>via headless service
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>via headless service

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 1: Distributed PyTorch Training Job Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create PyTorchJob<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: PyTorchJob added
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create headless Service<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod + Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Note right of Controller: Injects MASTER_ADDR, MASTER_PORT,<br/>WORLD_SIZE, RANK env vars

    Workers->>DNS: Resolve master pod DNS<br/>UDP/53
    DNS-->>Workers: Master Pod IP
    Workers->>Master: torch.distributed connection<br/>TCP (per job config)
    Master-->>Workers: Training coordination

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 2: MPI Job Communication Pattern

    participant Launcher as MPI Launcher Pod<br/>kubectl-delivery init
    participant MPIWorkers as MPI Worker Pods

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create MPIJob<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: MPIJob created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (hostfile + scripts)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher + Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Note right of Launcher: Init container copies kubectl<br/>binary from kubectl-delivery image
    Launcher->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec into workers<br/>HTTPS/443, per-job SA Token
    K8sAPI->>MPIWorkers: exec: mpirun commands<br/>RBAC: pods/exec on specific pod names
    MPIWorkers-->>Launcher: Training results
